@startuml
title Privilege granularity — from coarse to fine

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

package "Coarse: root/user duality" {
  [root\n(all privileges)] as root
  [user\n(no privilege)] as user
}

package "Middle: SUID / SGID" {
  [SUID binary\nruns as file owner] as suid
  [SGID binary/dir\nruns as / inherits file group] as sgid
}

package "Fine: capabilities" {
  [CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE\nbind ports < 1024] as bind
  [CAP_NET_RAW\nraw/packet sockets] as raw
  [CAP_NET_ADMIN\ninterfaces, firewall, routing] as admin
  [~40 other CAP_* units] as other
}

root --> suid : split a task off\nfrom all-or-nothing
user --> suid
suid --> bind : decompose root\ninto single rights
sgid --> raw
suid --> admin
sgid --> other

note bottom of root
  Two levels only: a SUID-root tool
  gets ALL of root just to do one job.
end note

note bottom of bind
  setcap cap_net_raw+ep /usr/bin/tcpdump
  grants exactly one right, no SUID-root.
end note
@enduml
